ASABA – Tragedy struck on Friday in Onicha Ugbo, Aniocha North Local Government Area, Delta State, when a 65-year-old woman, Mrs Joy Bioseh, was allegedly shot twice and macheted by one Agi Nwaicha over a disputed farmland. The DAILY INDEPENDENT source, Chinedu Bioseh, who is the son of the victim, revealed that his mother was attacked on New Year day at about 1 am, by the suspect who also hails from Onicha Ugbo town. He said it is only by God’s grace she will survive the attack, as “my mother is in serious pains, though with forlorn hope of surviving.” ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said his mother collapsed and fainted with blood gushing out of her while the boy escaped, thinking she was dead. According to Chinedu, the suspect’s family had been dragging “our farmland which resulted in the attack”. Crossover Service: Taskforce Scores Churches High On COVID-19 Compliance 2021, Year Of The Valley – Dr. Olukoya “Our farmland is what the boy’s family is dragging with us, yesterday night the boy lost his twins brother, and then he (the suspect) thought that we have hand in the death of his brother. “My mum went to church and came back around 1 am only to find out that the boy was waiting for her with a gun, he shot my mum twice and then used battleax on her.” He said the mother is currently bedridding in an unclosed hospital for Medicare while the case was incidented at Issele-Uku Police Station. At the time of filing the report, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Onome Onovwakpoyeya could not be reached for comments as she was busy her line when calls were put across to her, but a senior police officer confirmed the incident. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION